Hurricane Rosa threatens Phoenix, Las Vegas and Salt Lake City with significant flooding (drought areas could benefit)
It's not unusual for a tropical depression to hit Arizona, but that's exactly what's likely to happen early next week when what's left of Hurricane Rosa passes through the southwest desert, with the consequent risk of flooding.
The National Weather Service has already issued flood warnings for Monday and Tuesday in western Arizona to southern and eastern Nevada, southeastern California and Utah, including the cities of Phoenix, Flagstaff, Las Vegas and Salt Lake City.
The Rosa is expected to make its way directly to Phoenix on Tuesday and will make landfall on Monday night with rain.
