It is therefore expected to make landfall in Mexico with tropical storm strength on Monday afternoon or evening.
Precipitation in different parts of Mexico could be heavy, with a considerable risk of flooding.
According to weather.com, 75 to 150 mm of rainfall is expected from Baja California to northwest Sonora, with the possibility of up to 250 mm.
After that, Rosa will head north through Mexico in tropical storm strength, before reaching the Arizona border early Tuesday morning in tropical depression strength, finally crossing the state of Arizona and reaching southern Utah late Tuesday night.
The main risk we expect from Rosa or what's left of it is very heavy rainfall in Baja California, northwest Sonora and the desert of the southwest USA, according to the National Hurricane Center.
