Prime Minister Zaev claims that NATO membership will be accompanied by more than necessary investments in Macedonia, which has a unemployment rate of over 20%.
"I think the vast majority will vote for it, because more than 80% of citizens are in favour of the EU and NATO", Zaev pointed out before depositing his paper.
Zaev stated that a yes would be the confirmation of our future.
