It is increasingly evident that divergent opinions are not tolerated in the Labour Party, and each opinion is judged on whether it is acceptable to the party leadership.
This started shortly after Jeremy became the leader, as colleagues who I thought shared a similar political vision with before expected me to turn around and take positions that I would never have taken, whether it was on national security or the EU single market.
Whenever I speak in public, whatever I say, social media is filled with aggressive messages calling for my candidacy not to be renewed, denouncing the politics of the centre and telling me I shouldn't be in the Labour Party.
And it's not just me.
