The European team won the crown again when Danish captain Thomas Bjorn's team reached the 14.5 points needed to win the United States.
American star Phil Mickelson, who fought through most of the tournament, threw the exit shot into the water at the par 3 16 hole, which gave the victory to Francesco Molinari.
Italian golfer Molinari excelled in all of his series and became one of only four players to achieve 5-0-0 since the tournament's current format began in 1979.
American Jordan Spieth was sent off with a 5&4 by the less qualified European team player Thorbjorn Olesen, from Denmark.
The most qualified player in the world, Dustin Johnson, lost 2-1 to Ian Poulter of England, who could have played his last Ryder Cup.
